      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic constitutive model with nonlinear geometry and frictional contact justified by literature and preliminary material coupon testing. Sensitivity of QoIs to model form assumptions documented.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) exhibits linear elastic behavior below yield; screw geometry is explicitly meshed from CAD. Frictional contact at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces modeled with Coulomb friction (mu=0.2) consistent with published tribological data. Sensitivity study varying friction coefficient ±50% showed <3% QoI change. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
