      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly relevant to clinical failure modes (fatigue, fracture) and regulatory submission requirements under ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics used in 510(k) submissions. All three QoIs are directly linked to the clinical risk of implant fracture leading to revision surgery. Required Gradation 3 achieved."
